<!DOCTYPE html>
<link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>
<h1>HTML Guide</h1>
<h2>Comon HTML tags<span style="color: red;"> outside </span>&ltbody&gt.</h2>
<p>Click <a href="index.html">here</a> to go to body page.</p>



<table style="width:60%">
	<tr><!--table row-->
	<th style="width:20%;">Tag</th>
	<th style="width:40%;">Definitions</th>
	<th style="width:40%;">Examples</th>
	</tr>
	
	<tr>
	<td>&lt!DOCTYPE html&gt </td><!--table data-->
	<td>Used to set the type of document.</td>
	<td>&lt!DOCTYPE html&gt </td>
	</tr>

	<tr>
	<td>&lthtml lang="en"&gt </td><!--table data-->
	<td>Used to set language.</td>
	<td>&lthtml lang="en"&gt.</td>
	</tr>
	
	<tr>
	<td>charset </td><!--table data-->
	<td>Used to specifie the character encoding for the HTML document.</td>
	<td>&ltmeta charset="UTF-8"&gt</td>
	</tr>
	
		<tr>
	<td>title </td><!--table data-->
	<td>Sets the name of the page's bar.</td>
	<td>&lttitle&gt </td>
	</tr>

	<tr>
	<td>&lttr&gt</td><!--table data-->
	<td>Used to make sections in a table.</td>
	<td>This rectangle in this table is an example of &lttr&gt</td>
	</tr>
	
	<tr>
	<td>margin</td><!--table data-->
	<td>Used to put spaces between the edges of your website and the screen side.</td>
	<td>This document uses a margin.</td>
	</tr>
	
		<tr>
	<td>favicon </td><!--table data-->
	<td>Used to set an icon on the page's bar</td>
	<td>The icon on this page is a star.</td>
	</tr>

</table>